caption: Vinny D's is THE place to get italian beef (or anything else for that matter). The beef is as juicy as it is flavorful. Add in the nice spice from the giardiniera? It's a match made in flavor heaven. Fries were immaculate; italian ice to die for. The best thing about Vinny D's, though - the service. Truly wonderful people. I meant to take a picture of the food, but it smelled so good I could wait! This is place is a can't-miss!

I popped in tonight and they were closed. BUT Vinny D himself, very friendly, after a long day opened the window back up. Turned the patio lights on and offered us some Italian ice. Even let us sample some flavors. The best Italian ice!! Definitely coming back and you should too!
The Gelato was so good, so many options to choose from. The staff was super friendly and kind as well.
Shaved ice was great!
Good place for shave ice and good food
THIS WAS OUR FIRST TIME HERE. MY DAUGHTER SAW IT ON TIK TOK. THAT SHAVED ICE WAS EVERYTHING. THE BEEF AND FRIES WERE GREAT. THE OWNERS WERE EXTREMELY NICE!!!!!!!! WE ARE DEFINITELY GOING BACK!!!

Absolutely delectable ice cream! Creative flavors - graham central station and biscotti cookie together are spectacular. The choco chunks in graham central are crispy and lovely. Great flavors and very nice owners!
We loved Vinny D’s! It’s a must-visit if you’re looking for a great Chicago dog. And the service is awesome - quick and friendly!

Love this place! Travel all the way from Glenwood just to get it. The owner is so sweet and really puts hard work into his business. Not only do I love the shaved ice with ice cream but the food is bomb too. Try to Italian Beef! The peppers are his own recipe, very yum!

Visited this evening. The gentlemen there was very generous and polite, expressing his gratitude for my visit during winter which is usually a slow time for ice cream/gelato places! The gelato was also exceptional as well!
A Wicker Park staple for extremely solid hot dogs, chicken tenders, and shaved ice. Family owned and operated by the nicest guys in the world!
One of the best spots in the neighborhood!

Ok listen here. We don’t usually leave reviews, but it’s time this is said. This is probably the friendliest, best, most delicious place around Chicago. Their beef is amazing, their fries are killer, and their gelato is a home run! Vinny is one of the nicest and coolest owners ever and runs this place great! Don’t listen to all these fake reviews of haters, these people seek out issues and are just haters. They hate him because they’re jealous of his hard work and success. If you’ve ever eaten here, please do a favor a leave a good depth 5* review if you think it’s worthy!
BEST PLACE TO EAT. FOOD IS HOT AND ICE CREAM IS DELICIOUS.

This is one of the best places I've ever gone to eat. The staff and owner is extremely helpful and fast paced to fill your order. We were out in the cold with our son because I didn't know it was a walk up and they were so kind to let us wait in the inside door for our food. They are definetly a family restraunt and I can't ever see myself going anywhere else for gelato or Italian beef again. Hands down the best place I've ever been to.
Definitely worth checking out if you find yourself on this side of town. Can never go wrong with an italian beef sandwich anywhere in this City!
I decided to try out their gelato and it was absolutely disgusting!!I wish I took a picture but I threw it out the window the first second I tasted it.DO NOT GO TO!!!!!!!
You absolutely need to come check this restaurant out! It’s amazing and you will be hooked! Awesome service and food!
Amazing service, everyone seemed very friendly, quite fast service as well, love the staff and the ice cream is to die for!
Vinny is an awesome guy and his restaurant and food are beyond excellent.  10/10 on all fronts and I would highly suggest giving this place a try if you havent already!
Wonderful staff and excellent food!  The owner is just the cherry on top of the experience at this place.  If you are looking for a place to try, this should definitely be added on your list!
Owner of this restaurant is extremely kind and it shows upon his  business ethics and his employees.  Would highly recommend this restaurant to anyone!
Best italian beef ever hands down
Best ice cream I’ve had in a long time . Staff is also really nice and service is really good .
Best gelato hands down! The hot dogs are to die for and I will definitely be coming back when I have a chance. Vinny was very polite and treated me like a friend during my visit. 10/5 stars

Best  place i have ever been to hands down need to stop here with family friends or even by yourself! The employees are super respectful and polite and is hands down one of my favorite places to stop!
Best gelato I’ve ever had in Chicago. And the owner, Vinny, was super helpful and very respectful. Definitely would recommend this place if you’re ever in town! One hell of a menu too!
Bad customer service
Best shaved ice I've ever had. Melts in your mouth and there's no lumps. It's even and smooth. Owner is really nice too.  The expresso gelato is good too!
Great owner and the oreo blizzard goes great plopped into the center of the cherry shaved ice!
A Division street staple. Always great sausages, hot dogs, fries, and ice cream - you can’t go wrong!

Trust me, you’re gonna wanna try this guy’s beef. This is definitely the best Italian beef I’ve ever eaten, out of any Chicago stop (Johnny’s, Portillo’s, etc). His home made giardiniera is also fan-freakin-tastic! The service is great and he’s super friendly. Great portions on the fries too so pick up an order of those!
Ok, this guy is the best & the food is KILLER!
My family went to Chicago from Columbus on 11/28/20. The customer service was awesome and the food was amazing. VinnyD's is the place to visit me and my family will be coming back.
Love their Italian ice!
Great Italian Beef!
Everything was amazing
Such delicious ice cream in the city! Friendly staff & nice outside sitting
This is such an amazing place to hangout 😎! Ice cream is great and the service is awesome!

This place is fantastic. The gelato flavor and consistency is excellent. Since Amarino closed we haven’t been able to find anywhere that had proper gelato. This is it. The Italian ice is also impeccable. The beef sandwich was left off the tribunes list of go to’s but it’s similar in style to Johnnys Beef and Portillos. Great new spot, help these people out in these tough times and swing by!

A new shaved ice discovery for us, since our neighborhood favorite, Snow Dragon, shut its doors.  The owners’ energy is contagious coupled with their sexy and sassy love for their business makes this our new go-to. Great place and service!

Food was decent - ice cream looked pretty sad for $7 - really icey, gritty and apparently previously melted - maybe an issue w the cooler? I added a picture of what the ice cream was supposed to look like.

Italian ice and gelato in Ukrainian Village. our first time here and due to COVID-19, walk up window only and a 15 minute wait prior to ordering. many flavors to choose from and also have sandwiches and fries on the menu. tried the Superman, Nutella/Italian Cookie Gelato and Blue Raspberry Italian Ice. found that it's best to eat on premise as open scoops don't do well in 10 minute car rides. the Blue Raspberry held up, but the gelatos were a soupy.

The staff was so friendly and had the BEST customer service. It was a real family vibe with the interactions the employees had with each other as well as with the locals. Customer service is a real make or break for me and they definitely made it! Thanks guys!
Absolutely wonderful place to grab a bite or some shaved ice. Owner and employees are friendly and love dogs. A pup cone is a great way to treat you pet on a hot day during a walk.
Amazing dogs, great fries and fantastic service!

I was riding through my old neighborhood  and saw Italian ice sign. Decided to go in and Vinny is very nice and love his place of establishment  Vinny D. He gave me and my daughter  a great sample and he mixes Italian ice. I am going back when weather is warm.

I've been coming here since this place was new, and I feel that this place never ceases to amaze me. The people are really nice, the food is good, and the gelato is out of this wold. I am so excited whenever I go to this place because it has a welcoming feeling. The price is right and the people are warm. I will be back soon!

We also tasted the Italian cookie gelato which was outstanding-if we weren’t headed to dinner I probably would have had some of that too.
The owner is very kind. Must try the gelato and Italian Ice. Is open all year compared to other places in the Chicago area. Affordable prices. Great food.

Best Italian beef in Chicago! Owner is the best, he really took great care of us and he has so much passion in what he does! I got a side of waffle fries with chili and cheese on top and they were so crispy and delicious! The chili was homemade and so flavorful. caption: This is my go-to spot for when i want something good to eat on the quicks, especially good in Wicker Park since everything else in the neighborhood takes about 10min or more to make. Great prices too! I LOVE their gelato & their shaved ice for when i want something fresh to snack on. Tigersblood is my favorite!!! They recommended it to me the first time i went there when they first opened up. The staff is the best, literally the sweetest people. This is definitely my favorite place to go to when I'm in the neighborhood (which is almost everyday).
Best Italian beef I've had in Chicago by a wide margin. Highly recommend.

My boyfriend and I stopped in to VinnyD's on a hot Chicago Sunday afternoon - turned off by the ridiculous line at Jenni's not far away, we still wanted something refreshing and sweet.  VinnyD's hit the spot.  For starters the owner is quintessential Chicago. Midwestern hospitality combined with Italian American pride, he went above and beyond to help us taste test the best of what he had to offer.  His passion was evident and it clearly parlayed into a quality product.  The gelato and italian ice flavors are all hand picked by the owner and made especially for VinnyD's.  The gelato was flavorful but most importantly the correct texture; smooth and creamy just like in Italy.  The 21+ flavors with Jameson and Fireball were done well and tasted decadent versus like a bad frat boy night out.  My favorite however, were the Italian ices with flecks of fresh fruit seamlessly integrated into every bite.   I look forward to returning for a well priced, well made, well cared for treat!  Thanks VinnyD!

Great staff paired with some of the most refreshing Italian ice/gelato offerings I've ever tasted. Easy to call it the best I've had since living in Chicago (and quite possibly the best ive ever had). Already excited to get back!
Owners were really nice and the gelato was great on a summer night!  The Jamison flavor was especially good.
